The paper discusses an interactive learning task for navigation, which involves perception, planning, memory, exploration, and optimization. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on end-to-end navigation and reinforcement learning, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of Google Street View for photographic content also suggests a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Robotics (cs.RO) is also a possibility given the emphasis on interactive learning, and natural language processing (cs.CL) could be relevant if the navigation task involves language-based instructions.
